with version stable 1.6.3 1.6.2 1.6.1
with base    libX11 libpng
with role    video/television
with trait   x11
with source  http://www.goron.de/~froese/alevt/ http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/apps/video/ alevt-$VERSION.tar.gz
with info    last 20120311
with info    home http://www.goron.de/~froese/
with info    cite 'teletext/videotext decoder and browser for the bttv driver (/dev/vbi) and X11.

alevt is a teletext/videotext decoder and
browser for the bttv driver (/dev/vbi) and X11.
It features multiple windows, a page cache,
regexp searching, built-in manual, and more.
There is also a program to get the time from teletext
and one to capture teletext pages from scripts.'

build(){
 USAM=/usr/share/applnk/Multimedia

 sed -i "s:/usr/local:$DESTDIR/usr:" Makefile
 sed -i "s:-O2 -s:$CFLAGS:" Makefile
 make         &&
 mkdir -pvm 755               $DESTDIR/usr/bin &&
 mkdir -pvm 755               $DESTDIR/usr/man/man1 &&
 mkdir -pvm 755               $DESTDIR/$USAM &&
 make install &&
 cp $SCRIPT_DIR/AleVT.desktop $DESTDIR/$USAM
}
